==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bimetallism
<hw>Bi*met"al*lism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>bim⟦eacute⟧talisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The legalized use of two
metals (as gold and silver) in the currency of a country, at a fixed
relative value; -- in opposition to <xex>monometallism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The words <xex>bim⟦eacute⟧tallisme</xex> and
<xex>monom⟦eacute⟧tallisme</xex> are due to M. Cernuschi [1869].</note>
<rj><au>Littr⟦eacute⟧.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bimetallist</ent>⟦br⟧
